src\arbiter\__init__.py:3:The tool validates a mechanistic claim (gene -> T-cell program -> autoimmune disease)
src\arbiter\__init__.py:4:against real CD4+ T-cell Perturb-seq data, returning a verdict with a receipt per hop.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:7:### T1 — DE_stats.suppl_table.csv  (gene -> EFFECT)
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:11:- Effect categories: on-target KD 21,216 / no on-target KD 12,383 / putative off-target 384. `offtarget_flag` True in 2,837 rows.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:19:### T3 — cluster_autoimmune_enrichment_results.suppl_table.csv  (program -> DISEASE)
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:20:- **5,236 rows x 15 cols**; grain = cluster x disease x gene_set (unique). **77 clusters x 17 diseases x 4 gene_sets** (downstream_Rest/Stim8hr/Stim48hr + regulators).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:21:- 185 enrichments at p_adj_fdr<0.05. **924 negative-control rows** (`negative_control_disease=True`) — exclude from real hypotheses.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_qc_join_report.md:26:- **24,972** guides -> **12,604** genes (multiple guides/gene). `signif_knockdown` True in 54,094 rows; `high_confidence_no_effect_guides` in 7,002.
