docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:6:exact table value that justifies it**. Calibrated vocabulary only —
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:7:*supported / refuted / untested / flagged* — never "proven" or "discovered".
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:13:  never "no effect". This is the artifact catch.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:14:- **HOP 1 EFFECT (T1)** on-target KD status + `n_downstream` DE genes, with cross-donor /
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:15:  cross-guide reproducibility surfaced only where those columns are populated; `offtarget_flag`
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:19:- **HOP 3 DISEASE (T3)** membership in autoimmune-disease-enriched clusters; `intersecting_genes`
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:20:  is `ast.literal_eval`-exploded, `negative_control_disease` rows excluded, and the `gene_set`
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:21:  suffix aligned to the queried condition. `supported` requires FDR<0.05.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:25:### 1. EGR2 @ Stim8hr — receipt-backed YES (chain re-derived)
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:26:- **GATE supported**: 2/2 guides significant, best adj-p 1e-16 (guide expr 0.25 vs NTC 0.88).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:27:- **EFFECT supported**: on-target KD, effect size -11.06, **854 downstream DE genes**; cross-donor r=0.61, cross-guide r=0.79 (reproducible).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:28:- **PROGRAM supported**: Th1-associated in Hollbacker 2021 (log_fc 2.44, adj-p 0.049); not significant in Ota 2021 (adj-p 0.59) — **both contrasts reported**.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:29:- **DISEASE supported**: member of **34 significant disease clusters** across 13 autoimmune diseases; top hit asthma OR 20.4, FDR 5e-5.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:30:- **Overall:** *consistent with a validated gene -> program -> disease chain re-derived from the tables.*
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:32:### 2. IL2 @ Rest — the artifact catch (UNTESTED, not "no effect")
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:34:- Referee **halts at HOP 0**. IL2 is a canonical, biologically important gene that appears in both the Th program and disease gene-sets — a naive pipeline reading the empty downstream result would wrongly call it "no effect". The referee returns *untested — knockdown failed QC gate*, which is the correct, honest verdict.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:36:### 3. SLC1A5 @ Stim8hr — a plausible disease link REFUTED
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:37:- **GATE supported**: 1/2 guides significant (best adj-p 0.009).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:38:- **EFFECT refuted**: pooled `ontarget_significant=False`, only 1 downstream DE gene (a valid receipt-level disagreement with the single-guide gate, surfaced not hidden).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:39:- **PROGRAM supported**: Th1-associated in Ota 2021 (adj-p 0.001).
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:40:- **DISEASE refuted**: SLC1A5 appears in **9** disease cluster gene-sets but **none reach FDR<0.05** (best FDR 0.054, T1D, OR 2.73). The plausible-looking metabolic-gene -> autoimmunity link is **not supported by the enrichment data**.
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:41:- **Overall:** *gene->disease link refuted: gene in cluster gene-sets but enrichment not significant.*
docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07\pyzobot_referee_results.md:46:- Thresholds centralized (`SIG_ALPHA=0.05`); all statuses trace to a printed receipt value.
