**Verdict: keep-with-caveat.** NAB2 × atopic eczema is the right headline among these, but call it “near-novel, receipt-backed, Ota-supported” rather than pristine novel or fully replicated.

1. NAB2 chain is solid enough to feature. The shortlist has NAB2 × atopic eczema at `ac_lit=6`, `ac_known=0.0376`, `effect=301` in [lbd_questions_Stim8hr.json](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/lbd_out/lbd_questions_Stim8hr.json:45). The raw receipts support the claim: DE row is on-target, no off-target, `ontarget_effect_size=-16.8816`, `n_downstream=301`, strong reproducibility in [DE_stats.suppl_table.csv](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/DE_stats.suppl_table.csv:17870). Program is strong in Ota only: NAB2 Ota adj-p `1.95e-13`, z `7.71`; Hollbacker adj-p `0.2046` in [Th2_Th1...csv](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/Th2_Th1_polarization_signature_DE_results_full.suppl_table.csv:1596) and [line 25846](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/Th2_Th1_polarization_signature_DE_results_full.suppl_table.csv:25846). Exact disease evidence is real: atopic eczema clusters containing NAB2 at OR `3.90`, FDR `0.00283` and OR `3.43`, FDR `0.0224` in [cluster_autoimmune...csv](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/cluster_autoimmune_enrichment_results.suppl_table.csv:30) and [line 101](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/cluster_autoimmune_enrichment_results.suppl_table.csv:101). The negative effect-size sign is not a weakness; treat it as KD direction/effect metric, not disease direction.

2. Framing is mostly honest, but tighten “44 supported.” The funnel numbers are present in [sweep_Stim8hr.json](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/lbd_out/sweep_Stim8hr.json:13), and the build log’s NAB2 writeup matches the receipts in [docs/lbd-build-log.md](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/docs/lbd-build-log.md:137). But code-wise, `referee_triple` sets `answer="supported"` from exact-C disease classification alone, after resynthesizing `overall` separately; see [referee_triple.py](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/src/arbiter/lbd/referee_triple.py:109) and the proposer filter in [propose.py](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/src/arbiter/lbd/propose.py:78). My rerun of the 44 found 40 clean full-chain supported, 3 effect-flagged, and 1 effect-refuted row. So say “44 exact-disease survivors; 40 clean full-chain, 3 flagged, 1 refuted-effect artifact” if you want to be maximally clean. DNAJB9 is a good honesty example: off-target flag is real in [DE_stats](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/DE_stats.suppl_table.csv:7551). NUDT1 being pure-disjoint but weak is also correct: `effect=4` in [lbd_questions](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/lbd_out/lbd_questions_Stim8hr.json:31), and its Ota program adj-p is only `0.0381` in [Th2_Th1...csv](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/data/Th2_Th1_polarization_signature_DE_results_full.suppl_table.csv:7527). The EGR2-NAB2 note is legitimate as a hypothesis-strengthener, not as evidence. Keep it, but subordinate it to the receipt.

3. Red flags in the 44: yes. Ten rows have `effect: 0` yet get “consistent” because the base referee treats `ontarget_significant && n_downstream == 0` as EFFECT supported in [pyzobot_referee.py](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/docs/perturbseq-qc_2026-07-07/pyzobot_referee.py:214). That is bad for an LBD money-shot. Also, SBF2 appears in the ranked JSON with `overall: effect refuted`, which proves the `answer` filter is too loose. NAB2’s `ac_lit=6` is plausible as a low/noisy Europe PMC count, not obviously a substring artifact: symbols are quoted in [sources.py](C:/Users/wijesingheds/Documents/04%20Fun%20with%20Coding/2026-07-07%20PyZoBot-Arbiter/src/arbiter/lbd/sources.py:23). But it is not gene-normalized; I would not call those six hits “known NAB2-atopic eczema literature.”

4. Do not spend demo-critical time chasing Rest/Stim48hr before locking this story. Stim8hr is sufficient because it already gives a defensible near-novel candidate plus honest cull examples. If time remains, run the other conditions as a bonus screen or appendix, but first fix the wording/filter around the 44 and exclude zero-effect/flagged/refuted rows from “clean supported.”

Biggest risk in featuring NAB2: overclaiming novelty/mechanism. The data receipt is good; the vulnerable part is saying `ac_lit=6` means biologically established or cleanly curated literature, or implying the EGR2 corepressor relationship is part of the referee evidence.
